{{wikipedia}}
==English==
===Etymology===
[[Image:Split ananas.jpg|thumb|A split pineapple]]
[[Calque]] of Dutch ''[[sparappel]]'', '''[[pine cone]]''', from the resemblance of the fruit to a pine cone, as noted by Dutch importers of the fruit to Europe.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|pīʹnăpəl}}, {{IPA|/ˈpaɪnæpəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"paIn{p@l/}}
*{{audio|en-us-pineapple.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[tropical]] plant native to [[South America]], having thirty or more long, [[spined]] and pointed leaves surrounding a thick stem.
#The [[ovoid]] [[fruit]] of the pineapple plant, which has very sweet, white or yellow flesh, a tough, [[spiky]] shell and a tough, [[fibrous]] core.
#{{slang}} A [[hand grenade]].

====Synonyms====
*(''plant''): [[pineapple plant]]
*(''hand grenade''): [[grenade]], [[hand grenade]]

